cs.SE, cs.SD, cs.PL, cs.HC, cs.CY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper discusses requirements engineering in the context of agile software development. 
- cs.SD (Software Development) is also a likely category as the paper focuses on the practice and problems of requirements engineering in the context of software development. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper mentions the management of traces between requirements and code. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is a possible category as the paper discusses communication flaws as a common problem in agile requirements engineering. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a possible category as the paper touches on the topic of continuous improvement of requirements engineering due to intrinsic motivation, which could have implications for the social and ethical aspects of software development.
